    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If your java file runs in a linux machine println will use the linux standard \"\\n\"\nIf you want it to allways use \\r\\n, without changing system properties, simply replace your\nprintln(\"text\") with print(\"text\\r\\n\"). Or create a custom function printWindowsLine to do that</p>\n"
