    "last_activity_date" : 1763991748,
    "creation_date" : 1763991748,
    "answer_id" : 79828703,
    "question_id" : 6458657,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I ran into a problem with some code that was using println and print/printf with &quot;\\n&quot;. It worked fine in Linux but behaved inconsistently on Windows. I ended up removing each println and going with print/printf with &quot;\\n&quot; and worked as I wanted in Windows (think Git, MSYS2/Cygwin, WSL friendly).</p>\n<p>Another possible solution is to use of &quot;%n&quot; instead of &quot;\\n&quot; so it will use &quot;\\r\\n&quot; on Windows and &quot;\\n&quot; on Linux.</p>\n"
  } ],
